# Google Drive for Desktop ignore file (gitignore syntax).
# https://support.google.com/a/answer/14738509
#
# Purpose: prevent Drive from continuously syncing live SQLite database
# files. SQLite in WAL mode requires the .db / .db-wal / .db-shm triple
# to remain mutually consistent at every instant. Drive's per-file sync
# cadence violates that invariant and produced "database disk image is
# malformed" corruption (S311 incident, 2026-04-26).
#
# Backup intent is preserved for everything else (code, specs, bridge
# files, docs, KB python tooling). For DB backups, use either:
#   - manual VACUUM INTO snapshots committed to a non-live path, or
#   - the snapshot+upload daemon (future work, see GTKB-DB-BACKUP-001
#     when filed).

# --- Git internal directory (NEVER cloud-sync a .git/) ---
# A git repo's durable backup is its remote (origin), not file-level sync of
# .git/. Drive's per-file sync cadence races git's atomic loose-object writes
# and can drop/quarantine objects the repo still needs. On 2026-05-29 this
# produced a missing reachable blob (01448913, a historical lifecycle.py
# version) that broke `git gc`/repack on every commit -- the same failure
# class as the S311 SQLite corruption noted above. Excluding .git/ stops Drive
# from touching the object store. That incident was recovered non-destructively
# by restoring the object from origin.
.git/

# --- Live SQLite triples (the corruption trigger) ---
groundtruth.db
groundtruth.db-wal
groundtruth.db-shm
*.db-wal
*.db-shm

# --- Drive sync-conflict copies (Windows "(N)" suffix pattern) ---
groundtruth (*).db*

# --- DB backups generated by tooling (large + frequently rewritten) ---
groundtruth.db.backup-*
groundtruth.db.pre-backfill-*
groundtruth.db.corrupt-*

# --- ChromaDB persistent storage (also SQLite under the hood) ---
.groundtruth-chroma/

# --- Other local DBs that have caused issues historically ---
bridge.db
prime_bridge.db

# --- GT-KB runtime / ephemeral state (locks, dispatch-state, benchmarks) ---
# Drive's per-file sync cadence races the bridge-poller heartbeat/lock writes
# and produced "(N)" conflict-copy clutter (e.g. active-codex-session (3).lock).
# This tree is local runtime state, not durable project content -- the durable
# records live in MemBase and bridge/. Same failure class as the .git/ and
# live-SQLite exclusions above.
.gtkb-state/

# --- Drive's own staging directory (Drive normally hides this; redundant) ---
.tmp.driveupload/
